<li id="cite_note-SET-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-SET_17-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-SET_17-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Gould, S. J. (2002). <i><a href="/wiki/The_Structure_of_Evolutionary_Theory" title="The Structure of Evolutionary Theory">The Structure of Evolutionary Theory</a></i>. Cambridge: Belknap Press of <a href="/wiki/Harvard_University_Press" title="Harvard University Press">Harvard University Press</a>, p. 1018. <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-674-00613-5" title="Special:BookSources/0-674-00613-5">0-674-00613-5</a></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Gould_dep-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Gould_dep_18-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Gould_dep_18-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Gould, S. J. (1981). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.antievolution.org/projects/mclean/new_site/depos/pf_gould_dep.htm">"Official Transcript for Gould’s deposition in McLean v. Arkansas."</a> (Nov. 27). Under oath Gould stated: "My political views tend to the left of center. Q. Could you be more specific about your political views? A. I don't know how to be. I am not a joiner, so I am not a member of any organization. So I have always resisted labeling. But if you read my other book, <i>The Mismeasure of Man</i>, which is not included because it is not about evolution, you will get a sense of my political views." p. 153.</span>
</li>
