<li id="cite_note-109"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-109">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">In 1981 <i>The Mismeasure of Man</i> won the National Book Critics Circle Award for non-fiction. It was voted as the 17th-greatest science book of all time by <i>Discover</i> magazine vol. 27 (December 8, 2006); 9th-best skeptic book by <a href="/wiki/The_Skeptics_Society" title="The Skeptics Society">The Skeptics Society</a> (Frank Diller, "Scientists' Nightstand" <i>American Scientist</i>); and ranked 24th place for the best non-fiction book by the <a href="/wiki/Modern_Library" title="Modern Library">Modern Library</a>.</span>
